{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"W2\n    \n      Design with constraints · \"solve this without X\"\n      Drill mode variant. \"Design Parking Lot WITHOUT using inheritance.\" Or \"...without Singleton.\" Or \"...with only 6 classes max.\" Forces creative use of alternatives. Teaches when each pattern is actually necessary vs just familiar.\n      \n        🔒 Constrained Drill · Parking Lot\n        \n          🚫 You cannot use inheritance\n          🚫 Max 8 classes\n          ✓ Bonus: zero static fields\n        \n        Same problem. Different constraint set. Unlocks deeper pattern fluency.","choice":"w2","id":null,"timestamp":1776672559968}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"W5\n    \n      Temporal critique · review your OWN 6-month-old design\n      Unique opportunity: Architex remembers your past drills. 6 months later, prompts: \"Here's your Parking Lot design from May. What would you do differently now?\" You critique your past self. The most honest mirror in tech education.\n      \n        \n          🪞\n          \n            6-month mirror\n            Your Parking Lot · designed April 2026\n          \n        \n        \n          Past-you wrote: \"Used Singleton for ParkingManager. Felt right.\"\n          Score at the time: 68/100\n          Now with 6 more months of experience...\n        \n        \n          \"What would you critique if you got this as a PR today?\"\n        \n      \n      Most emotionally resonant feature possible. You see your own growth.","choice":"w5","id":null,"timestamp":1776672712365}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"W4\n    \n      Mutation testing · \"we broke something in this design · find it\"\n      Given a correct Observer diagram. System silently mutates it — removes unsubscribe(), changes inheritance direction, duplicates a class. \"Find the bug in 90s.\" 10 random mutations possible. Trains the debugging muscle.\n      \n        🔎 MUTANT HUNT · 0:45 remaining\n        \n          Subject+subscribe()+notify()\n          \n            Observer\n            +update()\n            ?\n          \n          ConcreteObs+update()\n        \n        Hint: something is missing from the Observer interface. What would break at runtime if you tried to clean up?\n      \n      Mutation types: removed method, wrong direction, duplicate, wrong cardinality, missing interface, broken constraint.","choice":"w4","id":null,"timestamp":1776672716675}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"W6\n    \n      Pattern-aware linter · npm install architex-patterns\n      Ship an ESLint plugin / Python linter. Detects anti-patterns in real code: god class, tight coupling, improper Singleton. Links to Architex lessons explaining what you could use instead. Brings Architex into the daily dev loop.\n      \n        \n          $ npm run lint\n          ⚠ architex/god-class · src/services/OrderManager.ts:1\n          Class has 47 methods. Consider splitting by responsibility (Strategy + Facade).\n          → Learn: architex.app/p/strategy\n          ✗ architex/missing-circuit-breaker · src/api/client.ts:12\n          3rd-party API call has no failure-threshold guard.\n          → Learn: architex.app/p/circuit-breaker","choice":"w6","id":null,"timestamp":1776672721008}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"W7\n    \n      Living reference solutions · community alternatives per problem\n      Official reference solution exists. Users submit alternative solutions too. Moderated, rated, displayed. Parking Lot gets 5 distinct community solutions — minimalist, enterprise, microservice, event-driven, functional. Learners see there's no \"one right answer\".\n      \n        📚 PARKING LOT · 6 SOLUTIONS\n        \n          \n            ⭐ Official · 12 classes · textbook · score 95\n          \n          \n            by @anshul-garg27 · minimalist · 6 classes · 2.1k upvotes\n          \n          \n            by @maya_l · microservice-ready · 14 classes · 1.4k\n          \n          \n            by @kenji_v · event-sourced · 10 classes · 800","choice":"w7","id":null,"timestamp":1776672740286}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"W8\n    \n      Hostile interviewer mode · AI grills you on your design\n      After you design. AI plays a skeptical senior engineer with attitude. 10 minutes of probing. \"Why is Payment a concrete class? Shouldn't it be an interface?\" · \"Your Singleton assumes single-process. Prove it doesn't break in my 8-server cluster.\" · \"You seem tired. Want to simplify?\" Realistic interview stress test.\n      \n        \n          😐\n          \n            Interviewer · minute 7/10\n            \n              \"I'm not convinced. You said 'I'd use Singleton because there's only one parking lot.' But at scale, you'll have multiple garages. How does your design handle that? And don't say 'we'll refactor later.'\"\n            \n          \n        \n      \n      Configurable aggressive level: friendly / standard / hostile / Jeff-Bezos-in-1999.","choice":"w8","id":null,"timestamp":1776672746230}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"W9\n    \n      Pattern mining in your git history · \"what patterns did you write this year?\"\n      Connect GitHub. Analyze your last 12 months of commits. Report: \"You wrote Observer 23 times. Factory Method 8 times. You've never written State or Flyweight. Here are 3 places in your codebase where State would help.\" Your annual pattern autobiography.\n      \n        📊 Your 2026 in patterns\n        \n          \n            Observer\n            \n            23\n          \n          \n            Factory\n            \n            8\n          \n          \n            Singleton\n            \n            5\n          \n          \n            State\n            \n            0\n          \n        \n        \n          \"You never wrote State this year. I see 3 switch statements in OrderProcessor.ts that are screaming for it. [Show me]\"","choice":"w9","id":null,"timestamp":1776672754611}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"W11\n    \n      \"Prescribe me a pattern\" · free-text problem → pattern recommendation\n      User types: \"I have a checkout flow with 5 different payment methods. Code is getting gross.\" AI responds: \"Sounds like Strategy. Here's why, here's the shape, and here's 10min to learn it.\" Takes real engineer pain → patterns that solve it. Reverse search: problem → pattern.\n      \n        \n          \"Every time we add a new shipping carrier we end up touching 6 files. It's becoming a mess.\"\n        \n        \n          \n            Strategy Pattern · 88% match\n            Encapsulate each shipping carrier, plug-and-play. You'd touch 1 file to add UPS.\n          \n          \n            Factory Method · 62% match\n            If instantiation is the pain point (not behavior).","choice":"w11","id":null,"timestamp":1776672768408}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"W12\n    \n      🔨 META DECISION\n      UI Revamp · do we rebuild or layer?\n      You asked: \"frontend UI revamp karna hai kyaa?\" Honest answer from live inspection:\n\n      \n        \n          ✅ What's already good (keep)\n          \n            · UML canvas is beautiful · A*-routed edges work · 4-panel layout is standard & clear · Pattern sidebar with category colors · Right-pane code tabs (TS/Py/Java) · Dark theme palette is sophisticated · Typography is solid\n          \n        \n        \n          🎨 What needs polish (layer)\n          \n            · Header & footer are thin / info-sparse · Right pane is text-wall (needs typography rhythm) · No mode switcher yet (Learn/Build/Drill/Review) · No persona-specific onboarding · No pattern constellation visual · Mobile is unusable currently\n          \n        \n        \n          ❌ What does NOT need rebuild\n          \n            · Canvas engine · A* routing · Dagre layout · Pattern catalog · Grading engine · Sidebar structure · Color system\n          \n        \n      \n\n      \n        💡 MY RECOMMENDATION\n        \n          Do NOT rewrite UI from scratch. Current UI is 80% production-quality. What Architex needs is additive:\n          1. Add the mode switcher (Learn/Build/Drill/Review pill in top chrome) — doesn't touch existing UI\n          2. Add the lesson column as Learn mode content (new layout)\n          3. Add Drill as a mode (reuses canvas + adds timer/grader wrapper)\n          4. Add Review as a 4th mode (minimal, phone-friendly)\n          5. Polish what exists — typography rhythm in right pane, status bar, mobile responsiveness\n          6. Layer on the delight moments (motion, illustrations, constellation)\n          Rebuild would be waste. 2 months of work for something that's already 80% there. Use those 2 months to ship Learn/Drill/Review modes + 90+ ideas from our batches.","choice":"w12","id":null,"timestamp":1776672780766}
